author: COMSOL
description: This model treats the movement of a beam by conducting a current through it to generate a temperature increase. This leads to a displacement through thermal expansion. The coupled thermal, electrical, and structural analysis makes it possible to estimate the current and temperature increase needed to displace the beam.
